                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre but regular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>First half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipits and headings of the texts
                           (occasionally in alternating red and black lines); short postscript to
                           the Gospel of Luke; the word mǝʿrāf, numbers, x-shaped signs and incipits
                           of the chapters; numbers of the “tituli”; some of the marginal notes
                           indicating liturgical occasions on which a given section should be
                           recited; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of the Ethiopic
                           numerals; names of the donors; chi rho and coronis.
 On the incipit
                           page of each Gospel, a few lines are rubricated (in groups of two lines,
                           alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
